\subsection{Subgroup diagram}
\begin{definition}\label{group.subgroup.diagram}
\uses{combin.hasse_diagram,group,group.order}
If $G$ is a {{KNOWL('group', 'group')}}, its **subgroup diagram** is the {{KNOWL('combin.hasse_diagram', 'Hasse diagram')}} for the set of subgroups of $G$ under inclusion.  Generally, subgroups of the same {{KNOWL('group.order', 'order')}} are drawn at the same height in the diagram.
\end{definition}


